# Fig. 01 — Pipeline Overview Diagram

**Status**: pending

## Caption draft

Figure 1. End-to-end pipeline for EEG source-level functional connectivity classification.
Raw EEG recordings (BIDS format) undergo preprocessing via MNE-BIDS-Pipeline (filtering,
epoching, artefact rejection). Source reconstruction projects the signal onto the cortical
surface using a dSPM inverse operator with fsaverage template (oct6, 8196 vertices).
Parcellation aggregates source estimates into ROI time courses using four atlases
(Desikan-Killiany 68 ROI, Destrieux 148, Schaefer-100, Schaefer-200). Spectral functional
connectivity is computed for seven metrics across five frequency bands. Features are
assembled into a classification matrix X and evaluated with GroupKFold cross-validation
(five algorithms). Balanced accuracy is reported with permutation-based significance testing.

